issues.suggested_fix:
Add both functions to the `SelectionContext` interface:
```ts
export interface SelectionContext {
  ...
  focusOnBounds: (bounds: Box3, padding?: number) => void;
  focusOnEntities: (entityPaths: string[]) => void;
}
```
And add them to the return statement:
```ts
return { setHovered, setSelected, refreshSelected, fitToView, flyToEntity, focusOnBounds, focusOnEntities, invalidateRect, dispose };
```

Refactor `fitToView` and `flyToEntity` to delegate to `focusOnBounds`:
```ts
function fitToView(): void {
  const box = new Box3();
  for (const mesh of getMeshes().values()) box.expandByObject(mesh);
  focusOnBounds(box);
}

function flyToEntity(entityPath: string): void {
  const mesh = getMeshes().get(entityPath);
  if (!mesh) return;
  const box = new Box3();
  box.expandByObject(mesh);
  focusOnBounds(box);
}
```
This makes `focusOnBounds` the single source of truth for the camera-positioning math.
